cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on measuring face-to-face interactions using RFID badges, which can be seen as a type of social network technology. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of human sensor technologies in behavioral studies. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper touches on ethical concerns related to the use of RFID badges in behavioral studies. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses data processing strategies to improve the validity of RFID badge measurements. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper compares RFID badge data with video data of the same interactions.
